# SwiftUI Patterns

## View Composition

### Standard View Structure
```swift
struct MyView: View {
    @Environment(AuthService.self) private var authService
    @Environment(AppState.self) private var appState
    @State private var viewModel = MyViewModel()
    @State private var isLoading = true

    var body: some View {
        NavigationStack {
            content
                .navigationTitle("Title")
                .task { await loadData() }
        }
    }
}
```

### Extract Complex Subviews
Break views into computed properties or child views when they exceed ~50 lines:
```swift
// Computed property for sections within the same file
private var headerSection: some View { ... }

// Separate struct for reusable or complex components
struct TaskRowView: View { ... }
```

## Navigation

### NavigationStack (primary navigation)
Use for drill-down flows within a tab:
```swift
NavigationStack {
    List(items) { item in
        NavigationLink(value: item) { ItemRow(item: item) }
    }
    .navigationDestination(for: Item.self) { item in
        ItemDetailView(item: item)
    }
}
```

### Sheets (modal presentation)
Use for create/edit forms, settings, and non-navigation flows:
```swift
.sheet(isPresented: $showSheet) {
    NavigationStack {
        EditView()
            .toolbar {
                ToolbarItem(placement: .topBarLeading) {
                    Button("Cancel") { showSheet = false }
                }
            }
    }
}
```

### FullScreenCover (immersive flows)
Use for onboarding, media viewers, and flows that need the full screen:
```swift
.fullScreenCover(isPresented: $showOnboarding) {
    OnboardingView(isPresented: $showOnboarding)
}
```

## State Management

### @State for view-local state
```swift
@State private var searchText = ""
@State private var isLoading = false
@State private var showSheet = false
```

### @Environment for injected services
```swift
@Environment(AuthService.self) private var authService
@Environment(AppState.self) private var appState
```

### @Bindable for mutating @Observable in body
```swift
var body: some View {
    @Bindable var state = appState
    Toggle("Setting", isOn: $state.someFlag)
}
```

### @AppStorage for UserDefaults persistence
```swift
@AppStorage("app_onboarding_completed") private var hasCompletedOnboarding = false
```

## Async Data Loading

### Use .task modifier (not onAppear + Task)
```swift
.task {
    await loadData()
}
```

### Retry on sheet/view appearance
```swift
// For views that might fail to load initially
.task {
    if items.isEmpty {
        await loadItems()
    }
}
```

## Common Mistakes

- Using `try?` for Firestore decoding (hides errors) -- use do-catch instead
- Using wrong asset names (e.g., `"profile-avatar"` vs `"ProfileAvatar"`) -- verify in Assets.xcassets
- Forgetting to add new files to the Xcode project (pbxproj)
- Modifying tab enum cases without updating ALL switch statements that reference them
- Using `.onAppear` with `Task {}` instead of `.task` (causes re-execution issues)
